    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good start. i've been reading some stuff about how cities like san francisco or nyc are struggling with housing costs though. so even with the benefits you mentioned, wouldn't high-density zoning actually make things worse for the people living there now since it drives up property values and causes gentrification?",
